g.text: A complete program (ProgramFile) consists of one or more program units. There is exactly one main
program which begins with a PROGRAM statement
This statement appears only at the beginning of the main program and the symbolic\nname main-name
must be unique (not used elsewhere in any of the program units).
There may also be any number of external procedures functions and subroutines) and BLOCK DATA
Every program unit must end with an END statement.
The BLOCK DATA statement identifies a subprogram
that initializes variables and arrays in labeled common
_LABEL_ can be optional but only one unnamed block
data subprogram can appear in the executable
The SUBROUTINE statement identifies a named program unit
as a subroutine, and specifies arguments for it:
- d: Variable name, array name, record name, or dummy
procedure name, an asterisk, or an ampersand.
The FUNCTION statement identifies a program unit as a function subprogram.
